---
title: Sweet Chili Chicken & Green Bean Stir-Fry 3 easy steps to a delicious dinner
description: This stir-fry is sweet, savory, a little spicy, and ready in just 15 minutes! You’ll sizzle juicy dark meat chicken with green beans in a flavorful mix of chili sauce and sweet soy glaze. Serve it over quick-cooking buttery rice, then finish with a shower of crunchy cashews for a rich, nutty finish.

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6785684028c218603675d595-4c9e1022.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6785684028c218603675d595-en-US.pdf
cuisine: East Asia
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-chicken-and-green-bean-stir-fry-6785684028c218603675d595
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
time required: 15 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 18 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 24 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 960 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; cut into 2-inch pieces.

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and drain off any
excess liquid.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine chicken, @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Stir until chicken is thoroughly coated.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green beans and coated chicken. Cook, stirring occasionally, until green beans are tender and chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @water{1/4%cup}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, and @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce} to pan. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Massage @microwavable rice{1} in package to break up grains. Transfer rice to a second
medium #microwave-safe bowl{}. Add @water{3%TBSP}; cover tightly with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until warmed through, ~{90%seconds} (microwave times may vary). Stir in @butter{1/2%TBSP} until melted.

Divide rice and stir-fry between shallow bowls in separate sections. Top with @cashews{1/2%ounce}. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.